Lancashire Police said that they are investigating an incident in which an officer told a member of the public that he would “make something up” in order to arrest the man.
It is unclear what the reason was for the altercation, in which the member of the public accuses the officer of “harassing” him.
We’ll do that shall we?,” the officer told the man, Lancashire Live reports.
The unnamed man protested his innocence, claiming that he had done “nothing wrong” — to which the officer replied: “I’ll make something up.
